description:
Come On You Sea-Cooks
The big German liners which the Government is now fitting out as Army transports need a large
Commissary Staff, and the Navy wants American citizens and aliens of friendly nations with first papers
to serve as Cooks, Stewards and Mess Attendants on board these ships going abroad; men who are to
cook and prepare the food and serve it. Here is a first-class job and working for the Navy makes you
a better man. Your pay begins at once; you are never laid off because of bad business or hard times
and if you are sick you get your money just the same. In the Navy you associate with clean, high-
minded men under healthy conditions with plenty of things to eat and with a lot of sports and amuse-
ments. Remember, everything is free, board and lodging, and so is your first outfit of clothing. By
joining the Messmen Branch of the American Navy, you are not only helping your Country but also yourself.
- THIS IS WHAT YOU CAN EARN-
